Transforming Data

Notes:

Add a Scaling Layer

Notes:

library(gridExtra)
p1 = qplot(x=friend_count, data=pf, 
           fill=I('blue'), color=I('black'))
p2 = qplot(x=log(friend_count+1, base = 10), data=pf, 
           fill=I('red'), color=I('#000000'))
p3 = qplot(x=sqrt(friend_count), data=pf, 
           fill=I('green'), color=I('black'))
grid.arrange(p1,p2,p3, ncol=1)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

##same using ggplot
p1 = ggplot(aes(x=friend_count), data=pf) +
      geom_histogram()
p2 = p1 + scale_x_log10()
p3 = p1 + scale_x_sqrt()

grid.arrange(p1,p2,p3, ncol=1)
